<html><head><meta content="text/html;charset=utf-8" http-equiv="Content-Type"><meta content="utf-8" http-equiv="encoding"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, minimum-scale=1, maximum-scale=1"><title> Experiment  </title><script type="text/javascript" src="jquery-2.1.4.js"></script>          <script type="text/javascript" src="parameters.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="create_stim.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="init.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="show_stim.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="newtrial.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="evaluate.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="introspective_response.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="severalfunctions.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="./md5.js"></script><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="./styles.css"><script type="text/javascript">/*--------------------------------------*/$(document).ready(start);function start(){sc = init(sc); /*------load image----------------------*/imageObj = new Image();imageObj.src = './canvas.jpg';imageObj.onload = function() {	var canvasL = document.getElementById('myCanvasL');	var canvasR = document.getElementById('myCanvasR');	contextL = canvasL.getContext('2d');     // global variable	contextL.clearRect(0, 0, canvasL.width, canvasL.height);	contextL.drawImage(imageObj, 1, 1);	contextR = canvasR.getContext('2d');	contextR.clearRect(0, 0, canvasR.width, canvasR.height);	contextR.drawImage(imageObj, 1, 1);}$('#submit_button').click(function(){	$("#exp1").hide();	$("#exp2").hide();	$("#exp3").hide();	$("#exp4").hide();	window.scrollTo(0,0);	$('body').css('zoom','100%'); /* Webkit browsers */	$('body').css('zoom','1.0'); /* Other non-webkit browsers */	setTimeout('newtrial(sc)', 2000);	}); };    </script></head><body><DIV class="row" id="Stimuli" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; ">	<div class="col-2"></div>	<div class="col-3">		<canvas width="200" height="200" id="myCanvasL" ></canvas>	</div>	<div class="col-2"></div>	<div class="col-3">		<canvas width="200" height="200" id="myCanvasR" ></canvas>	</div>		<div class="col-2"></div></DIV>  <DIV class="row" id="DotC" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); ">	<div class="col-12" id="Dot"><p>.</p></div></DIV> 	<DIV class="row" id="Question1" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; ">	<div class="col-3"></div>	<div class="col-6" id="preg"><p>Where is the grating?</p></div>	<div class="col-3"></div></DIV> <DIV class="row" id="Question2" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; ">	<div class="col-3"></div>	<div class="col-6" id="preg_segu" ><p>How confident are you?</p></div>	<div class="col-3"></div></DIV><DIV class="row" id="bar1" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; ">	<div class="col-3"></div>	<div class="col-6" id="line1" style="background:#98bf21;"> </div>	<div class="col-3"></div></DIV><DIV class="row" id="bar2" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; ">	<div class="col-3"></div>	<div class="col-6" id="Dial" style="background:#98bf21;position:absolute;float:left;"> </div>	<div class="col-3"></div></DIV><DIV class="row" id="marks" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; ">	<div class="col-12" id="scale" style="position: absolute;"><p>50 %</p></div></DIV><DIV class="row" id="ResponseButtons" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; ">	<div class="col-3"></div>	<div class="col-2">		<button id="RespButton1" style="float:right" >Left</button>	</div>	<div class="col-2"></div>	<div class="col-2">		<button id="RespButton2" style="float:left" >Right</button>	</div>	<div class="col-3"></div></DIV><DIV  class="col-12"  id="Letterhead1" style="top:-40px"> <SPAN style="float:left;"><H3 style="color:#ff934d;margin-left:15px;">Study name</H3></SPAN>					 <SPAN style="float:right;"><H3 id = "Letterhead2" style="color:#ff934d;margin-right:15px;">Level 1</H3></SPAN></DIV><!--------instructions 1----- --><DIV class="row" id="exp1" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: block; "><CENTER><div class="col-3"></div><DIV class="col-6" id="te1">	<H2>Instructions </H2>	<HR>	<P>This study takes about half an hour. It is not difficult but it requires full attention. The study is composed by many trials, and each trial you will be asked two questions:<br>	</P><UL>	<LI>Whether a given image is presented at the right side or left side of your screen.</LI>	<LI>How confident you are on the choice you just made.</LI>	</UL>	<P>The following screens will show you a detailed description of the game.</P>	<P></P>	<HR>		<button class="button_instr" onclick="instructions(4);" style="float:right;">Next</button>	<br><br>	<br><br></DIV></CENTER></DIV><!--------instructions 2----- --><DIV class="row" id="exp2" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: none; "><CENTER><div class="col-3"></div><DIV class="col-6" id="te2">	<H2>Instructions</H2>	<HR>	<P>Each trial starts with a dot at the center of the screen for you to fixate. Next, two <b>patches of black and 	white dots</b> will be flashed at the left and right side of the screen. One of them -and only one- contains 	a <b>grating</b> embedded. Your first task is to decide which one of the two patches contains the grating. </P>    <img src="./example1.png" id="example1">    	<br>	<P> You have to respond "Right" or "Left" by clicking (or tapping, if you use a touchscreen) on the response buttons showed below.</P>    <img src="./example2.png" id="example2">	<HR>	<button class="button_instr" onclick="instructions(1);" style="float:left;">Back</button>	<button class="button_instr" onclick="instructions(3);" style="float:right;">Next</button>	<br><br>	<br><br></DIV></CENTER></DIV><!--------instructions 3----- --><DIV class="row" id="exp3" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: none; "><CENTER><div class="col-3"></div><DIV class="col-6" id="te3">	<H2>Instructions</H2>	<HR>	<P>After that you will have to report your <b> confidence</b> on the Left/Right decision you just made. 	To report your confidence level, slide the mouse on a continuous scale ranging from 	"not confidence at all", to "fully confident" and click to report the confidence level. If you use a touchscreen, just tap on the position you	want to choose on the scale.</P>	<P>The response bar looks like this:</P>    <img src="./example3.png" id="example3">                    <P>You start at <b>Level 1</b>, and the objective of the game is to reach higher levels by responding correctly. 	You will know your overall performance at the end of the game.</P>	<P>Confidence level is not taken into account to calculate your performance, there is not 'correct response' for confidence: just report how sure you are on your decision 	in the most accurate way you can. Also, some trials are easier than others, you may sometimes feel you are guessing the location of the grating. That's ok, 	in that case just report a low confidence level.</P>	<HR>	<button class="button_instr" onclick="instructions(2);" style="float:left;">Back</button>	<button class="button_instr" onclick="instructions(4);" style="float:right;">Next</button>	<br><br>	<br><br></DIV></CENTER></DIV><!--------instructions 4----- --><DIV class="row" id="exp4" style="color:rgb(0, 55, 0); display: none; "><CENTER><div class="col-3"></div><DIV class="col-6" id="te4">	<H2>Ready to go!</H2>	<HR>	<form name="personales" action=""  method="POST"  id="form1">	<P><SPAN style="display:inline-block;width:100px;">Name:</SPAN><INPUT length="64" name=Name id="Name" value="" onkeyup="validateFields();"> <SMALL>* at least 4 characters</SMALL></P>	<P><SPAN style="display:inline-block;width:100px;">Gender:</SPAN><SELECT id="Gender" name=Gender onchange="validateFields();"><OPTION value="nr" selecte="selected"> I prefer not to answer</OPTION><OPTION value="m" selecte="selected">Male</OPTION><OPTION value="f">Female</OPTION></SELECT> <SMALL>*</SMALL></P>	<P><SPAN style="display:inline-block;width:100px;">Age:</SPAN><INPUT length="2" id="Age" name=Age onkeyup="validateFields();"> <SMALL>*</SMALL></P>		<P>You have a <br>	&thinsp;&thinsp;&thinsp;<input type="radio" name="Input" value="Touchscreen"  onchange="validateFields();" > Touchscreen	<br>	&thinsp;&thinsp;&thinsp;<input type="radio" name="Input" value="Mouse"  onchange="validateFields();" > Mouse <br></P>	<P><SMALL>* Input required</SMALL></P>		</form>	<p><input type="checkbox" onchange="validateFields();" id="consent_checkbox" />I have read the <a href="./conditions.html"  target="_blank">Conditions</a>, I agree to take part in this study.</p>	<HR>	<button class="button_instr" onclick="instructions(3);" style="float:left;">Back</button>	<button class="button_instr" onclick="validate_send();" style="float:right;" id="submit_button" >Start</button>	<!--<button class="button_instr" onclick="validate_send();" style="float:right;" id="submit_button" disabled >Start</button>---->	<br><br>	<br><br></DIV></CENTER></DIV></body></html>